Christopher John Francis Boone is the narrator and protagonist of the novel. Fifteen-year-old Christopher                 is mathematically gifted struggles for social acceptance and understanding as a                 result of his apparent autism. He views the world largely in absolutes, dividing his                 life experience into a series of extreme likes and dislikes. He feels most                 comfortable with logic and order, making Wellingtonâ€™s murder an irresistible puzzle                 for him to solve. He resides with his father and pet rat Toby at 36 Randolph                 Street.